{
  "texts": [
    "8 The AIA even proposes to ban certain AI practices because they pose unacceptable risks.",
    "9 The PRC then followed a sectoral approach by adopting three laws related to AI, with a specific focus on algorithmgenerated recommendations, deep synthesis technology, and generative AI.",
    "10 Last, the global race to the regulation of AI heated up with the adoption of an executive order by US President Biden.",
    "11 At the same time, serious problems were identified with the current narrative of a so-called \"global race toward the regulation of AI,\" which was even framed as a \"battle of digital empires\" to regulate technology.",
    "12 This rhetoric seems wrong and counterproductive for several reasons and should, therefore, be replaced by one calling for a \"race toward the global regulation of AI\" instead."
  ]
}